      "id": "52618",
      "title": "IRE Journal: Q2 2013",
      "description": "This issue of The IRE Journal focuses on investigating animal welfare. It features stories about using data reporting to dig up the history of Palm Beach puppies, how horse-racing data points to animal deaths and injuries, the cost of baby elephants in the zoo, and the saga of greed that led to the death of a wild jaguar. This issue also features the 2012 IRE Award winners. Check out some of the best investigative projects of the year.\n\\n\n\\nThe Journal is included with IRE membership. Members may download full, archived issues of the Journal for free. <strong>Nonmembers may purchase a digital copy for $10.</strong>",
