    {
      "id": "83888",
      "title": "Beyond Chi Square",
      "description": "Sometimes it's important to know whether a pattern could be a fluke. Is a stockbroker lucky or trading on insider knowledge? Did a player throw a game or have a bad streak? Is the lottery rigged or could the same person win twice?\\n\\nReporters often turn to traditional methods like a chi-square test to determine statistical significance, but other techniques, from poisson distributions to monte carlo simulations, might be a better fit. This PowerPoint presentation will walk you through some of the methods you can use to answer the question: is it a fluke?",
      "category": "tipsheet",
      "tags": [
        ""
      ],
      "downloads": [
